
[1]slightly

   SLIGHTLY, adv.

   1. Weakly; superficially; with inconsiderable force or effect; in a
   small degree; as a man slightly wounded; an audience slightly affected
   with preaching.

   2. Negligently; without regard; with moderate contempt.
